<h3 class="text-center mt-4 mb-4">Bulk Upload Products</h3>

<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-md-8 col-lg-6">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="card-text">Upload a CSV file to add products records. The CSV should have the following columns:</p>
                    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-4">
                        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>brand_name</strong> - Name of the Brand (case-insensitive)</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>device_name</strong> - Name of the Device (case-insensitive)</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>category_name</strong> - Name of the Category (case-insensitive)</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>product_name</strong> - Name of the product (case-insensitive)</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>sku</strong> - Sku of the product (case-insensitive)</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>variant</strong> - Variant</li>
                        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>country</strong> - Country code e.g us for United States </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item"><strong>model number</strong> - Model Number e.g A2633	 </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="text-muted">Each row in the CSV represents an inventory item for a specific seller and product. Ensure the email and product fields match existing records in the system.</p>
                    <div class="mb-4">
                        <div class="mb-4">
                            <a href="/sample_products.csv" class="btn btn-secondary">Download Sample CSV</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <%= form_with url: import_csv_admin_products_path, local: true, multipart: true do |f| %>

                    <div class="">
                        <div class="">
                            <%= f.file_field :file, accept: ".csv", required: true, class: "" %>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="d-flex justify-content-end">
                        <div class="d-flex col-2 justify-content-end p-0">
                            <%= f.submit "Upload CSV", class: "btn btn-primary py-2" %>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <% end %>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>